  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1633970271810-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1633970271810-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1633970271810-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1633970271810-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1633970271810-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and add the <strong>halved green beans</strong> to the pot</p><p>Cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice and green beans are cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving – this is your <strong>green bean rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1633970277292-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1633970277292-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1633970277292-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1633970277292-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1633970277292-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice and green beans are cooking, peel and roughly chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic </strong>and<strong> ginger</strong></p><p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pod[s] </strong>open by squashing them with the side of a knife and discard the <strong>outer green pod[s]</strong></p><p>Grind the<strong> chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>cardamom seeds</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>black pepper</strong> (freshly ground is best!) and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>in a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> to form a coarse paste – this is your <strong>spice paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1633970282066-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1633970282066-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1633970282066-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1633970282066-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1633970282066-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the<strong> chopped creamed coconut</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> then add your <strong>fish sauce</strong> – this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
